    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_220458">Check out this idea.  I posted it on VN last week and sent it to Mythic with a link to the post on a public forum since I know they can't take direct suggestions for fear of copy write infringement.  Anywho, please give this the intelligent and insightful consideration that I have seen in the past on this board:<br />
<br />
Veil Fungi, Prismite, and Truesilver <br />
<br />
This concept seems well within the capabilities of Mythic and NF and would solve a several key problems with the current game mechanics.  In some cases it will get people to return to the game because it will reinstate a play style that is currently lost.<br />
<br />
This concept will augment the following:<br />
<br />
Open field RVR<br />
Increase the value of Player crafted equipment<br />
<br />
The essence of this concept is that 3 new crafting agents are introduced that only appear in RVR… one in each realm.  For the sake of this disortation, I will call them Veil Fungi, Prismite and Truesilver.<br />
<br />
Veil Fungi: Hibernia (look like animist mushrooms except they use the texture from the veil rift and don’t fight, you just run up and cut them down and they turn into 10 bags)<br />
Prismite: Midgard (look like crystals, which you just tank down like an enemy node or font and it turns into 10 bags when it has no more hp)<br />
Truesilver: Albion (looks like a big puddle of silver colored water which you collect in alchemist vials.  You can left click on it to see how much is left.)<br />
<br />
If anyone doesn’t like these names or the nature of the resource, please don’t get hung up on it… the point is that there are 3 resources, one per continent.<br />
<br />
Each resource spawns in one of 3 locations on the continent (so it is possible to avoid a larger zerg and still make your rounds) at random intervals between 4 hours and 24 hours.  These locations are all away from towers or keeps.  A spawn is between 75 and 125 units of the resource.<br />
<br />
These resources are added to player made weapons and armor to augment them.  They each do something different.  One increases the total number of slots for SC on the item. One increases the total value of SC the item can hold (SC is limited by 2 factors: number of gems the item can hold and the total value of the augmentation) The last one adds a second Alchemy slot to the item.  The amount of the resource required to augment an item varies… Perhaps a jerkin requires 20 Veil Fungi while gloves require 5 to augment.<br />
<br />
So far, it is all good… right?<br />
<br />
Here is the catch… due to the delicate nature of these resources, a player can only carry one at a time if they are using speed.  Carrying more than one is possible but prevents you from using speed.  You can not stealth while carrying more than one of the resource either.  If you are killed while carrying the item in NF, you drop it and the enemy can pick it up.<br />
<br />
What this does is motivate people to participate in small group open field RVR in all 3 realms.  It feeds the end game, it isn’t just fluff… and it helps crafters compete with the new uber drops and artifacts.  If you try to hunt the resource in the zerg, it is likely you are missing out on the other 2 resources… it will be wiser to have 8 man scouting parties cruising the spawn points.  It may be that you cruise all night and never happen to catch a spawn, but you will surely run into some open field action.<br />
<br />
One of the spawn points should definitely be on the plateaus in each continent because currently there isn’t a lot of reason to go up there.  One of the spawn points should be in the agro forest of each continent.  None of the spawn points should be in areas with low level mobs as this just promotes gray ganking.  The third spot on each continent should be planted relative to where the other 2 are so that a triangle path is formed (i.e. they are not all in a strait line, defeating the purpose of having 3 and not 2).<br />
<br />
From what we have seen with TOA, it is certainly possible for DAOC to have rare spawns that don’t always spawn in the same spot… i.e. traitors dagger, BoS, etc.  These items will be expensive, but the structure curtails a single powerful class hoarding the resource.<br />
<br />
I would extend this idea to each of the lower bgs.  However, at lower levels, there would only be one resource that spawns at one of 3 locations since the bgs are much smaller and lower level player crafted items don't really have to compete with TOA items.  It doesn't matter to me what this item increases, the fun will be in collecting it.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
