    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_221622">An interesting take on the whole Art's Vs Player Crafted argument.  One thing I can add to that is the whole leveling aspect of Arts.  That does frustrate everyone.  One way to &quot;level&quot; that playing field would be to make the art level comparable to your level.  IE, allow the arts to be available from particular levels - level 40 perhaps, and eash level you achieve, they gain a level as well.  If you get an art at lvl 44, then your art will be lvl 4.  This could be tied into the back story that as you improve yourself, you unlock or able to use the additional benefits the arts give.  Thus, by lvl 50 you will have lvl 10 artifacts.<br />
<br />
For arts that you can get before lvl 40, give them 10 levels as well from the point you can activate them - so say Orion's belt will be lvl 10 to a level 45+ toon.<br />
<br />
I know that people who have spent the time and effort to level their arts the old way will probably complain about this, but in the end, it's about getting some balance between PC and Arts/TOA.  <br />
<br />
And while we are on the subject of PC items, I'd like to know when Armour Crafters are going to be able to make the designs that drop in the TOA and Catacombs?</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
